Hey,

I finally got to read Codex: Renegade Chapters. It was even worse than
advertised.
The stench of ignorance and apathy was eye-wateringly palpable.
I've only ever played Chaos in 40k (with a dash of GS Cult at one
point).
So, I can't see waiting 5yrs to play again, but the current 'offering'
is repellent to me.
Now, what's a poor Chaos player to do? Desperate times call for
desperate measures:

+++

Preheresy Legions

The Rant

For over a decade, 40k background has insisted that all of our weapons
and wargear are a jumble of mutant, obsolete JUNK. Despite this, we've
managed to stay competitive with the Darlings of the Studio on the
strength of our Daemonic Powers and Legion Specific Rules. Right up to
the present, this combo let us craft countless variations on the eight
Legions, with room for every conceivable &quot;Renegade Chapter&quot; in the
Black Book. But that's all gone now. We're left with just a watered-
down version of the Black Book, no Legions, and no Daemons capable of
fulfilling their former mission-critical roles.

The Horror

In &quot;Heart of Darkness&quot;, Colonel Kurtz famously suggests that a certain
clarity of thought is revealed to a mind that simply embraces The
Horror. Messrs Johnson and Thorpe, by their indifference, and their
thoughtless and dismissive words, have given me the impetus to embrace
the 40k version of The Horror. That Horror being, [sigh] the Space
Marine Codex. It's a measure of how truly awful the new Dex is, that
I'm even *considering* such a thing. Looking at the two books side-by-
side, I have to go with the lesser evil. YMMV.

Here's the Thing

Consider playing Chaos lists as though they represent Preheresy
Legions. This means using our Chaos models to represent a force from
@M30. Between Istvaan and the Siege of Terra, our Legions all shared
the same gear and weaponry as their Loyalist counterparts. Sometime
between 30k and 40k apparently, some of us lost our weapons, our
vehicles, our gear, our strength, our pride, our cunning, and ended up
as Renegade Chapters, the whimpering shadow of our former selves
represented in the new book. Tellingly, Loyalists still enjoy many of
the rules that have been ripped out of our Codex:

Retinues of Vets, Termis or just plain Marines.
Units of 5 Termis with 2 Reaper Assault Cannon.
(Autocannon represent &quot;preheresy&quot; Asscannon, obviously)
Termi Retinues are available, too.
Termi Tac Squad Champs are back!
All Combibolters become A2 Stormbolters.
Wargear is returned to its rightful place - The Armoury.
All the best Vehicle Upgrades are included, only cheaper.
Tons of Sorcerous Psi Powers - that don't suck.
Cheaper Predators.
Cheaper Plasguns.
HQ options that don't *all* cost 200-300pts.
Compare IC costs vs stats: Prince ~ Commander; Sorcerer ~ Librarian;
Lord ~ Chaplain

Warhammer 30k, Hardcore Edition

C:CSM implies that 40k Renegades abandon much of their nifty kit when
they break away. 30k Legionnaires abandon nothing. If we choose, we
can still field:

LR Crusaders.
Combiplas weapons.
Dedicated Assault Termis.
Plascannon and Multimeltas in Tac Squads.
Razorback Transports.
Cyclone MIssile Launchers.
Rending Skimmers.
Attack Bikes.
Techmarines and Servitors. (Iron Warrior players can have their Servo
Arms back!)
Veteran Skills to access cheap, Tank Hunting Lascannon!
Drop Pods. How long have we wanted these? Preheresy Legionnaires build
and take them.
Preheresy Legions Know No Fear, me Droogies!
Daemon models can represent Scouts - 18ppm for the same WS, S and A,
plus Move Thru Cover, Infiltrate, a 4+ armour save, BS4 and Sniper
Rifles? Talk about a bargain!

The Catch (What will we have to give up?)

Summoned Generic Daemons.
Gav rendered Lesser Daemons useless by dint of being weaker in assault
than the Marine Units required to Summon them. Why would I pay Marine
prices for a Unit with no ranged attack or armour save? I wouldn't.
I'd just take more Marines instead.
Generic GDs inevitably surrender VPs by killing my own Champions just
by arriving on the board. And, imo, 130pt forced-reserve CC models
that can't get movement bonuses, armour or decent weapons aren't
terribly tempting, anyway. Let's see, what else?

Defilers.
I'll just rename mine &quot;Whirlie&quot;, and get IF Barrage back. (Bas is
already renamed 'Vin')
Possessed.
Gee, an overpriced Unit whose effectiveness can't be guessed before
deployment. See ya!
Chosen.
This might be an issue if there weren't Infiltrators in the SM book.
There are - plenty.
Cult Marines.
I have seen the light - they're just Marines with Traits, right Gav?
Spawn.
Another overpriced random Unit. Except this one's random *and* non-
scoring! Buh-bye.
Obliterators.
[sigh] This one's the biggie for me. They'll just get promoted to
Termi Sergeants, I guess.
Special Characters.
This is another toughie. Our ultimate badasses relegated to generic
HQ's or skulking behind Secret Identities. Still, if they were real
soldiers, they'd probably opine, &quot;Renegade Chapters? Legionnaires have
chunks of guys like that in their stools!&quot;

Original Gangstas

I've put together a preliminary list of Legion Traits, in case
anyone's interested.
Mesdames et monsieurs, the Legions of Legend:

Alpha Legionnaires are Sombre and notably divergent -
'Don't Be Seen' gives Infiltrate and Acute Senses,
'Cleanse' gives the 2 AW option (Cultists = Scouts).
Drawback = 'Flesh' limits Heavy Support selections.

Death Guard are Stern, Courageous, significantly divergent -
'Cleanse' gives the 2 AW option,
'Trust' gives True Grit and Counterattack.
Drawbacks = 'Eye' limits Fast Attack selections, and
'Alone' means 'take no Allies'.

Emperor's Children are Dutiful and notably divergent -
'No Mercy' gives Furious Assault,
'Wargear' gives up to 6 Heavy Weapons squads.
Drawback = 'Glory' limits Terminator selections.

Iron Warriors are Wise and notably divergent -
'Scions' gets you Techmarine HQ (Warsmith),
'Wargear' gives up to 6 Heavy Weapons squads (Bas becomes Vin).
Drawback = 'Eye' limits Fast Attack selections.

NIght Lords are Courageous and Fierce, significantly divergent -
'Don't Be Seen' gives Infiltrate and Acute Senses,
'Blessed Warriors' gives them up to 6 Assault squads.
Drawbacks = Flesh' limits Heavy Support selections, and
'Alone' means 'take no Allies'.

TSons are Pious and Wise, significantly divergent -
'Suffer Not Heretics' gives Tank Hunters,
'Wargear' gives up to 6 Heavy Weapons squads.
Drawbacks = 'Glory' limits Terminator selections, and
'Alone' means 'take no Allies'.

Word Bearers are Pious and Courageous, significantly divergent -
'Suffer Not Heretics' gives Tank Hunters (Apostle = Chaplain),
'Don't Be Seen' gives Infiltrate and Acute Senses,
Drawbacks = 'Eye' limits Fast Attack selections, and
'Alone' means 'take no Allies'.

World Eaters are Fierce and notably divergent -
'Take It To Them' gives them back their BP/CCWs,
'Blessed Warriors' gives them up to 6 Assault squads.
Drawback = 'Flesh' limits Heavy Support selections.

The Happy Ending

Doubtless, there are some details that I've overlooked, but this
should be enough to provide food for thought. Some may feel that Codex
BA or Templars, etc, better fits the theme of their Legion. Well, if
so; have at it. I'm just pointing out a possible, albeit horrific
option to try and help bring some of the zest back into lists that
have, imo, been drained of their former life and color by certain
indifferent authors.

Obviously, The Horror is a temporary measure to keep our lists
interesting and unpredictable until GW comes to its senses and recalls
every copy of the Gavdex for ritual incineration and burial. Failing
that, it's going to be a long, long haul until the next Codex, and the
thought of only seeing the same three Chaos lists every game for five
years is just completely unacceptable. Of course, the SM Dex could get
'harmonized' in the meantime. If that happens, we'll just fall back
and regroup, but let us never tolerate the Legions being forgotten!

To those players who choose to embrace The Horror, I feel obliged to
add that you must consider the likelihood that Loyalist Space Marine
players of every stripe will view your Legio Whirlwinds and Drop Pods
etc, with fear and loathing, and, possibly, even some  measure of
hate. I have considered this possibility, and on reflection find that,
considering the alternative, I actually kinda look forward to some of
that.

Is that Chaotic, or what?    }|B&gt; ]

Playa
